---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Badge from '../components/Badge.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../components/SectionLabel.astro';
import TestimonialBlock from '../components/TestimonialBlock.astro';
import HourglassIcon from '../components/HourglassIcon.astro';
import ChessKnightIcon from '../components/ChessKnightIcon.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Builder — Add AI Revenue to Your Agency in 12 Weeks"
  description="The Reis IA Builder program gives you a sellable AI offer, a client acquisition system, and your first project delivered — in 12 weeks."
  activePage="builder"
>

  <!-- SECTION 1: HERO -->
  <section class="relative bg-black pt-32 pb-24 md:pt-20 md:pb-16 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Chess grid texture -->
    <div class="chess-grid absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-100" style="mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, black 30%, black 70%, transparent);" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <!-- Chess knight decorative -->
    <div class="absolute right-[5%] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 hidden lg:block pointer-events-none text-white opacity-[0.06]" aria-hidden="true">
      <ChessKnightIcon size={250} />
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0 relative z-10">
      <!-- Chess pre-headline (ADDED 2026-03-11) -->
      <p class="text-[13px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-accent mb-4">
        For Agency Owners Ready to Stop Reacting to AI — and Start Positioning Ahead of It
      </p>

      <!-- Chess headline variation B (ADDED 2026-03-11) -->
      <h1 class="text-[40px] md:text-[56px] lg:text-7xl font-bold leading-none tracking-tighter text-white max-w-[900px]">
        AI without strategy is guessing.<br />
        12 weeks from now, you could be playing a completely different game.
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-normal leading-relaxed text-neutral-400 mt-6 max-w-[640px]">
        The Reis IA Builder program gives you a sellable AI offer, a client acquisition system, and your first project delivered — in 12 weeks. With direct support from someone who has built this from scratch.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10">
        <Button variant="hero" href="#apply">Apply for the Next Cohort &#8594;</Button>
        <p class="text-[13px] text-neutral-500 mt-3">Spots are limited. Next cohort: <span class="placeholder-content px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">[DATE]</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sticky CTA bar (desktop only, shown after scroll) -->
  <div
    id="sticky-cta"
    class="hidden lg:flex fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-40 bg-neutral-950/90 backdrop-blur-md border-t border-neutral-800 h-[72px] items-center translate-y-full transition-transform duration-300"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-8 w-full flex items-center justify-between">
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400">Next cohort: <span class="text-white font-medium">[DATE]</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Limited to 12 clients</p>
      <a href="#apply" class="bg-accent text-black text-sm font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-accent-hover transition-all duration-200">
        Apply Now &#8594;
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    const stickyCta = document.getElementById('sticky-cta');
    const heroSection = document.querySelector('section');
    const footer = document.querySelector('footer');

    if (stickyCta) {
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (!entry.isIntersecting) {
              stickyCta.classList.remove('translate-y-full');
              stickyCta.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'false');
            } else {
              stickyCta.classList.add('translate-y-full');
              stickyCta.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
            }
          });
        },
        { threshold: 0.1 }
      );
      if (heroSection) observer.observe(heroSection);
    }
  </script>

  <!-- SECTION 2: PROBLEM / AGITATION -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 py-24 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0">
      <div class="max-w-[720px]">
        <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[42px] font-semibold text-white leading-tight" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
          Your Competitors Are Already Selling AI. Here's What That Means for You.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>You've seen it.</p>
          <p>An agency you know — maybe a smaller one — just rebranded around AI services. Their prices went up. Their clients are loyal. They're winning work you used to win on reputation alone.</p>
          <p>Meanwhile you're watching.</p>
          <p>Not because you don't understand the opportunity. You do. AI is the biggest shift in the agency world since social media, and you know exactly where it's going.</p>
          <p>The problem isn't the technology.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-white font-semibold">The problem is you don't have a packaged offer, a clear delivery process, or a sales conversation that closes — and building that from scratch is a full-time project while you're already running a full-time agency.</strong></p>
          <p>You've probably tried some version of this already:</p>
        </div>

        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
          {[
            'Watched dozens of hours of AI tutorials and still don\'t know what to sell',
            'Experimented with ChatGPT, Make.com, or n8n and hit the limits of figuring it out solo',
            'Pitched a "we do AI" capability to a client — and then had to scramble to deliver it',
            'Priced an AI project by guessing, left money on the table, and weren\'t sure how to structure the next one',
            'Lost a client — or almost lost a client — to an agency that moved faster',
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
              <span class="text-neutral-500 mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true">—</span>
              {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-4 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>That's not a knowledge problem. That's a structure problem.</p>
          <p>You don't need more tutorials. You need a framework, a methodology, and someone who's already built the path — so you stop experimenting and start earning.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Market data callout box -->
        <div class="mt-8 bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-8">
          <p class="text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            The bottom 60–70% of digital agencies will face a race to the bottom within 2–3 years. Not because they're bad at their work. Because they haven't differentiated.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-4">AI projects sell for $5,000–$20,000.</p>
          <p class="text-[17px] text-neutral-300 mt-2 leading-relaxed">
            Agencies that sell them are adding new revenue streams on top of existing retainers — not replacing them. The window is open right now. But it's not staying open.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Hourglass variation closer (ADDED 2026-03-11) -->
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
          <p class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            <HourglassIcon size={20} class="text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <span>Here's the cost that doesn't show up on any invoice. Every month you wait, a competitor closes an AI client you could have closed. Every month you wait, the learning curve gets compressed — but so does the opportunity window. Every month you wait, the agencies who moved earlier are adding case studies, raising prices, and locking in clients on retainer.</span>
          </p>
          <p class="text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed pl-8">Time doesn't just pass. It compounds — in their favor.</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-white pl-8">The real cost of waiting isn't money. It's the time you can't get back.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: SOLUTION REVEAL -->
  <section class="bg-black py-24 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0">
      <div class="max-w-[720px]">
        <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[42px] font-semibold text-white leading-tight" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
          This Is What the Reis IA Builder Program Was Built For.
        </h2>

        <!-- Chess variation opening (ADDED 2026-03-11) -->
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>Think of it this way.</p>
          <p>A course gives you pieces. Builder teaches you to play the game.</p>
          <p>Every week, you're not just learning AI — you're positioning. Structuring your offer. Mapping your market. Building the sales system. Delivering the first project. Each step is intentional. Each module moves you closer to a revenue position your competitors haven't claimed yet.</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">We don't build AI. We position the right pieces before moving.</p>
          <p>That's what separates agencies who close AI clients from agencies who "do AI."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison table -->
      <div class="mt-12 max-w-[800px] relative">
        <div class="chess-grid absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none rounded-lg opacity-100" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden relative z-10">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 bg-neutral-850">
            <div class="px-5 py-4 text-[13px] uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400">Course</div>
            <div class="px-5 py-4 text-[13px] uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">Builder</div>
          </div>
          {[
            ['Information', 'Application'],
            ['Passive watching', 'Weekly working sessions'],
            ['Generic templates', 'Your specific offer, priced, packaged, ready'],
            ['Solo implementation', 'Direct support on your first 1-2 client projects'],
            ['You figure out clients', 'Client acquisition system built during the program'],
            ['Credential, no revenue', 'Revenue before you finish'],
          ].map(([course, builder]) => (
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 border-t border-neutral-800">
              <div class="px-5 py-4 text-[15px] text-neutral-500">{course}</div>
              <div class="px-5 py-4 text-[15px] text-white">{builder}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-8 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed max-w-[720px]">
        Builder is built for people who are serious about adding AI as a real revenue stream — not people looking for something to add to their LinkedIn.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 4: PROGRAM DETAIL -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 py-24 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0">
      <SectionLabel>The Program</SectionLabel>
      <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[42px] font-semibold text-white mt-4 leading-tight" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
        The Builder Program: 12 Weeks, Four Modules, One Goal — Revenue.
      </h2>

      <!-- Chess variation intro (ADDED 2026-03-12) -->
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-neutral-400 mt-4 max-w-[720px] leading-relaxed">
        Think of the 12 weeks as a game played in four moves. Most agencies lose at AI not because they lack skill — but because they make moves without a position. Builder reverses that. Every module is a deliberate move. Each one builds your position before you advance to the next.
      </p>

      <!-- Module blocks -->
      <div class="mt-12 space-y-12">
        {[
          {
            num: '01',
            title: 'AI Offer Architecture',
            subtitle: 'The opening move. You can\'t win a game you haven\'t set up.',
            weeks: 'WEEKS 1–2',
            body: 'Before you can sell AI, you need to know what you\'re selling. Most agencies make the mistake of saying "we do AI" — and that\'s not a sellable offer. It\'s a category.',
            bullets: [
              'Map your specific market and identify the highest-value AI opportunities for your clients',
              'Structure your AI offer — deliverables, positioning, pricing, and presentation',
              'Create your offer documentation: proposal template, pricing calculator, scope framework',
              'Walk out with a specific, packaged AI service your agency can sell this week',
            ],
            showChess: true,
          },
          {
            num: '02',
            title: 'Client Acquisition',
            subtitle: 'Position before you advance. An offer without prospects is just a document.',
            weeks: 'WEEKS 3–4',
            body: 'An offer without a sales system is just a document.',
            bullets: [
              'Build your outreach and prospecting system — LinkedIn, email, referral paths',
              'Develop content that attracts AI buyers to you (instead of you chasing them)',
              'Master the AI sales conversation — how to frame the value, handle objections, close on outcome',
              'Run your first live sales conversations with real prospects — with coaching on what to adjust',
            ],
            showChess: false,
          },
          {
            num: '03',
            title: 'Implementation Framework',
            subtitle: 'Execute with precision. You\'ve sold it — now deliver it right.',
            weeks: 'WEEKS 5–8',
            body: 'Now you sell it — and you actually deliver it.',
            bullets: [
              'Learn the Revenue-First implementation methodology — build the right thing, not just something',
              'Set up your delivery infrastructure: tools, processes, templates, quality checks',
              'Deliver your first AI client project — with Reis IA as your direct technical and strategic backup',
              'Document the delivery so every future project is repeatable and scalable',
            ],
            showChess: false,
          },
          {
            num: '04',
            title: 'Scale and Systemize',
            subtitle: 'Endgame. Turn one win into a system that keeps winning.',
            weeks: 'WEEKS 9–12',
            body: 'Turn one client into a pipeline. Turn one delivery into a process.',
            bullets: [
              'Build a referral and repeat system — so AI revenue doesn\'t stop when your outreach does',
              'Structure delivery so it\'s not founder-dependent — you can bring in support as you scale',
              'Explore the Reis IA Partners pathway — sell AI projects you can\'t deliver alone, with Reis IA as your implementation backbone',
              'Plan the next revenue milestone with a documented system behind it',
            ],
            showChess: false,
          },
        ].map((module) => (
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[48px] font-bold text-accent leading-none">{module.num}</span>
              {module.showChess && (
                <ChessKnightIcon size={24} class="text-accent mt-3" />
              )}
            </div>
            <div class="lg:border-l lg:border-neutral-800 lg:pl-8">
              <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">{module.title}</h3>
                <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-400 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">{module.weeks}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-accent-muted italic mb-3">{module.subtitle}</p>
              <p class="text-base text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">{module.body}</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2">
                {module.bullets.map(bullet => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
                    <span class="text-accent mt-1" aria-hidden="true">—</span>
                    {bullet}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Deliverables block -->
      <div class="mt-16 bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-8">Everything That Comes With the Program</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Core Deliverables</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Weekly live sessions (group calls or 1:1 — tier dependent)',
                'Full access to Reis IA\'s AI implementation templates, frameworks, and SOPs',
                'Direct WhatsApp and Slack access to Moroni for questions between sessions',
                'Implementation support on your first 1–2 client projects',
                'Lifetime access to the Reis IA Network community',
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-300">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M13.854 3.646a.5.5 0 0 1 0 .708l-7 7a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-3.5-3.5a.5.5 0 1 1 .708-.708L6.5 10.293l6.646-6.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0z"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Bonuses Included</p>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Pre-built AI proposal templates (editable, ready to send)',
                'AI project pricing calculator',
                'Objection handling scripts for AI sales conversations',
                'Reis IA Partners pathway upon program completion',
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-300">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M8 1.5a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3zM5 3a3 3 0 1 1 6 0A3 3 0 0 1 5 3z"/>
                    <path d="M6.5 7.5A.5.5 0 0 1 7 7h2a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v6a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V8H7.5A.5.5 0 0 1 6.5 7.5z"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 5: WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="bg-black py-24 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0">
      <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[42px] font-semibold text-white text-center mb-12" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
        Is Builder Right for You?
      </h2>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- For You -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">This Program Is For You If:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {[
              'You run a digital agency or service business and you\'re serious about AI as a revenue stream',
              'You\'ve been curious about AI but keep getting stuck on what to sell, how to price it, or how to deliver it',
              'You\'re losing clients or leads to AI-enabled competitors — or you can see it coming',
              'You\'re willing to do the work: show up, implement, and close real clients during the 12 weeks',
              'You have the budget to invest in your agency\'s growth and you understand that one AI client pays for the program',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-300">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 0 1-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 0 1 1.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 0 1 1.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Not For You -->
        <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">This Program Is NOT For You If:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {[
              'You\'re looking for a shortcut or a passive income scheme — Builder requires real work',
              'You expect Moroni to run your agency for you — this is mentorship, not outsourcing',
              'You\'re not yet generating any revenue in your business — Builder is an accelerator, not a starter kit',
              'You\'re just "AI curious" with no intention to implement — this is a results-focused program, not an education experience',
              'You\'re looking for the cheapest option — Builder clients are serious about ROI, not about finding a deal',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500/50 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 0 1 1.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 1 1 1.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 0 1-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 0 1-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 6: OBJECTION HANDLING -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 py-24 md:py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px] px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-0">
      <SectionLabel>Common Questions</SectionLabel>
      <h2 class="text-[28px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[42px] font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-12" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
        Let's Address What You're Really Thinking.
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-[800px] space-y-10">
        <!-- Objection 1 -->
        <div class="pb-10 border-b border-neutral-800" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #262626 20%, #262626 80%, transparent); background-size: 100% 1px; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-position: bottom;">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Can I really sell AI if I'm not technical?</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            <p>This is the most common question — and the most important misconception to clear up.</p>
            <p>The best AI sellers are not the most technical people. They are the best business strategists.</p>
            <p>Your job as the agency owner is to identify the revenue opportunity in a client's business and sell the outcome. The technical implementation is the execution layer — and that's exactly what the Builder program teaches you to structure, partner, or deliver through the Reis IA ecosystem.</p>
            <p>83% of tech leaders outsource at least part of their AI initiatives. Even the technical people outsource. You don't need to understand neural networks. You need to understand where AI makes money — and that's a business strategy skill, not a coding skill.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Objection 2 -->
        <div class="pb-10 border-b border-neutral-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What if I don't get clients during the program?</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            <p>The program is structured specifically to prevent this.</p>
            <p>Module 2 is dedicated entirely to client acquisition. You'll build your outreach system, run live sales conversations, and get direct coaching on what to adjust. By Week 4, you should have active prospects in your pipeline.</p>
            <p>And if you complete every module and still don't have a sellable AI offer? Full refund.</p>
            <p>We stand behind this because the methodology works — and because we only accept people we believe will put in the work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Objection 3 -->
        <div class="pb-10 border-b border-neutral-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Is $4,000–$15,000 too much to invest right now?</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            <p>Let's do the math.</p>
            <p>One AI project sells for $5,000–$20,000.</p>
            <p>The Builder program pays for itself on your first client — often before the program ends.</p>
            <p>The real question is: what does 12 more months of waiting cost you?</p>
            <p>Every month agencies are adding AI services, raising their prices, and taking clients who used to consider you. That cost is invisible but real.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Objection 4: Hourglass variation (ADDED 2026-03-12) -->
        <div class="pb-10 border-b border-neutral-800">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <HourglassIcon size={20} class="text-accent flex-shrink-0" />
            What if I don't have time while running my agency?
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-[17px] text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
            <p>Builder is designed for founders with existing businesses — not students with unlimited time.</p>
            <p>Sessions are structured, not open-ended. Templates and frameworks cut the time it would take to figure this out alone by 80%. And the program is designed to generate revenue during the 12 weeks — so it pays for the time it requires.</p>
            <p>If you can commit 5–8 hours per week for 12 weeks, you can do this.</p>
            <p>Here's the real time question. Not "do I have 5–8 hours a week for 12 weeks?" — because you do, if you look at what those hours currently produce. The real question is: what does the next 12 months look like if you spend them the same way you spent the last 12?</p>
